Leader election is required when there is a single node responsible for writes (leader/primary).

1) Coordinator-Based Election

    Leader sends heartbeats → Coordinator detects failure (heartbeat timeout) 
    → Coordinator checks cluster state → Coordinator selects best replica 
    → Promotes it to leader → Updates routing / metadata

    Fast and deterministic
    Coordinator SPOF


2) Consensus-Based Election

    Leader crashes → Followers time out → Followers become candidates (after random timeout) 
    → Request votes (each node votes only once per term) 
    → Majority wins (votes ≥ N/2 + 1) → New leader starts

    Fully decentralized
    Strong correctness guarantees


3) Manual / External Election

    Monitoring detects failure → Human/script decides promotion 
    → Replica is promoted manually → Traffic is redirected via config/DNS/LB

    Slow & Human Error

